XSD: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>${liquibase.lf}<!-- This schema describes a simple notification.  It only contains a content${liquibase.lf}element which is a String...about as simple as one can get -->${liquibase.lf}<schema xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"${liquibase.lf}  xmlns:c="ns:notification/common"${liquibase.lf}  xmlns:cs="ns:notification/ContentTypeSimple"${liquibase.lf}  targetNamespace="ns:notification/ContentTypeSimple"${liquibase.lf}  attributeFormDefault="unqualified" ${liquibase.lf}    elementFormDefault="qualified">${liquibase.lf}  <annotation>${liquibase.lf}    <documentation xml:lang="en">${liquibase.lf}      Simple Content Schema${liquibase.lf}    </documentation>${liquibase.lf}  </annotation>${liquibase.lf}  <import namespace="ns:notification/common" schemaLocation="resource:notification/notification-common" />${liquibase.lf}  <!--  The content element is just a String -->${liquibase.lf}  <element name="content">${liquibase.lf}    <complexType>${liquibase.lf}      <sequence>${liquibase.lf}        <element name="message" type="c:LongStringType"/>${liquibase.lf}      </sequence>${liquibase.lf}    </complexType>${liquibase.lf}  </element>${liquibase.lf}</schema>
XSL: ${liquibase.lf}${liquibase.lf} ${liquibase.lf} ${liquibase.lf} ${liquibase.lf} ${liquibase.lf} ${liquibase.lf} ${liquibase.lf}

XSD: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>${liquibase.lf}<!-- This schema defines an generic event notification type in order for it${liquibase.lf}to be accepted into the system. -->${liquibase.lf}<schema xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:c="ns:notification/common" xmlns:ce="ns:notification/ContentTypeEvent" targetNamespace="ns:notification/ContentTypeEvent" attributeFormDefault="unqualified" elementFormDefault="qualified">${liquibase.lf}  <annotation>${liquibase.lf}    <documentation xml:lang="en">Content Event Schema</documentation>${liquibase.lf}  </annotation>${liquibase.lf}  <import namespace="ns:notification/common" schemaLocation="resource:notification/notification-common" />${liquibase.lf}  <!-- The content element describes the content of the notification.  It${liquibase.lf}  contains a message (a simple String) and a message element -->${liquibase.lf}  <element name="content">${liquibase.lf}    <complexType>${liquibase.lf}      <sequence>${liquibase.lf}        <element name="message" type="c:LongStringType"/>${liquibase.lf}        <element ref="ce:event"/>${liquibase.lf}      </sequence>${liquibase.lf}    </complexType>${liquibase.lf}  </element>${liquibase.lf}  <!-- This is the event element.  It describes a simple event type containing a${liquibase.lf}  summary, description, location, and start/stop times -->${liquibase.lf}  <element name="event">${liquibase.lf}    <complexType>${liquibase.lf}      <sequence>${liquibase.lf}        <element name="summary" type="c:NonEmptyShortStringType" />${liquibase.lf}        <element name="description" type="c:NonEmptyShortStringType" />${liquibase.lf}        <element name="location" type="c:NonEmptyShortStringType" />${liquibase.lf}        <element name="startDateTime" type="c:NonEmptyShortStringType" />${liquibase.lf}        <element name="stopDateTime" type="c:NonEmptyShortStringType" />${liquibase.lf}      </sequence>${liquibase.lf}    </complexType>${liquibase.lf}  </element>${liquibase.lf}</schema>
